1
00:01:10,207 --> 00:01:11,207
Dad.

2
00:01:11,657 --> 00:01:12,657
This is my Dad.

3
00:01:13,511 --> 00:01:14,757
I know what I should do next.

4
00:01:14,757 --> 00:01:16,086
Hello there.

5
00:01:16,086 --> 00:01:17,614
I'm Chai's co-worker.

6
00:01:17,614 --> 00:01:18,332
Oh?

7
00:01:18,332 --> 00:01:20,589
And also, his bed buddy.

8
00:01:20,589 --> 00:01:21,755
Huh?

9
00:01:21,755 --> 00:01:22,921
What are you doing, Tid-Gift?

10
00:01:22,921 --> 00:01:26,397
You already slept with her, so take responsibility!

11
00:01:26,397 --> 00:01:26,673
What's up?

12
00:01:26,673 --> 00:01:28,384
That P, he contacted me.

13
00:01:28,384 --> 00:01:29,854
He said we wouldn't make it.

14
00:01:29,854 --> 00:01:30,842
Shit!

15
00:01:30,842 --> 00:01:32,676
Hey, is this really happening, All-New?

16
00:01:33,070 --> 00:01:34,343
If I don't shoot, we won't survive.

17
00:01:34,343 --> 00:01:35,343
I think we got away.

18
00:01:37,212 --> 00:01:38,212
But I don't think so.

19
00:01:43,583 --> 00:01:45,583
What are we doing here, All-New?

20
00:01:45,772 --> 00:01:46,772
He'll find us.

21
00:01:50,345 --> 00:01:51,334
What exactly are you looking for?

22
00:01:51,334 --> 00:01:52,291
I'm looking for a gun!

23
00:01:52,291 --> 00:01:52,880
A gun?

24
00:01:53,352 --> 00:01:53,852
Yes.

25
00:01:54,307 --> 00:01:55,307
Shit, where the hell is it?

26
00:01:56,898 --> 00:01:57,898
Try calling Siri.

27
00:02:02,290 --> 00:02:03,290
There you go.

28
00:02:04,765 --> 00:02:05,956
Hello.

29
00:02:05,956 --> 00:02:08,147
1 fried oysters, please.

30
00:02:08,147 --> 00:02:08,735
And you?

31
00:02:08,735 --> 00:02:09,764
Pad-Thai with prawns.

32
00:02:09,764 --> 00:02:11,313
And 1 Pad-Thai with prawns.

33
00:02:11,313 --> 00:02:11,988
Who are you calling?

34
00:02:11,988 --> 00:02:13,017
Siri, the Oyster place.

35
00:02:13,017 --> 00:02:14,017
I told you to call our Siri.

36
00:02:15,252 --> 00:02:16,752
Well, I'm hungry.

37
00:02:18,366 --> 00:02:19,637
Excuse me, I'd like to cancel my order.

38
00:02:19,637 --> 00:02:20,508
Aren't you hungry?

39
00:02:20,508 --> 00:02:21,508
We'll eat later.

40
00:02:22,056 --> 00:02:23,056
Try calling our Siri.

41
00:02:25,051 --> 00:02:27,719
The number you dialed cannot be reached at this time.

42
00:02:27,719 --> 00:02:28,719
I can't reach her.

43
00:02:29,469 --> 00:02:30,469
Let's go somewhere else.

44
00:02:30,737 --> 00:02:32,809
Wait, found it.

45
00:02:32,809 --> 00:02:33,809
A gun?

46
00:02:34,082 --> 00:02:35,233
A talisman.

47
00:02:35,233 --> 00:02:38,222
Ugh, you got something better than that?

48
00:02:38,222 --> 00:02:39,733
C'mon, one for you and one for me.

49
00:02:39,733 --> 00:02:41,204
Man...

50
00:02:41,204 --> 00:02:44,034
Hey, found it!

51
00:02:44,034 --> 00:02:45,789
What is it? A gun?

52
00:02:45,789 --> 00:02:47,218
Hey, what the hell is that?

53
00:02:47,218 --> 00:02:48,218
Must be Madam Porn's weapon.

54
00:02:52,380 --> 00:02:53,380
Is it though?

55
00:02:58,771 --> 00:03:00,277
Shit, shit, shit.

56
00:03:00,277 --> 00:03:02,508
That P, he contacted me.

57
00:03:02,508 --> 00:03:03,508
He said we wouldn't make it.

58
00:03:04,498 --> 00:03:05,498
Shit!

59
00:03:09,253 --> 00:03:10,253
Man, finally.

60
00:03:12,801 --> 00:03:15,154
Hey, is this really happening, All-New?

61
00:03:15,154 --> 00:03:17,030
This should be able to protect us. Let's run.

62
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:18,030
How are we going to do that?

63
00:03:19,418 --> 00:03:20,418
I got a car.

64
00:03:21,204 --> 00:03:22,204
Okay, this should be our way out.

65
00:03:28,309 --> 00:03:31,309
All-New! Come on, let's run!

66
00:03:44,622 --> 00:03:46,018
No, no, no.

67
00:03:46,018 --> 00:03:47,018
They wouldn't see.

68
00:03:49,130 --> 00:03:52,130
I didn't go there. I'll be back next week.

69
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:57,155
Well, tell them...let them check...

70
00:03:57,155 --> 00:04:01,155
How many villages? How many subdistricts? Tell them.

71
00:04:03,563 --> 00:04:05,563
Who would know that?

72
00:04:06,775 --> 00:04:09,841
How would I know that? Who will take you there?

73
00:04:09,841 --> 00:04:14,072
Well, ask the person who will take you.

74
00:04:14,072 --> 00:04:15,941
Get a truck.

75
00:04:15,941 --> 00:04:18,691
No, it's not that way.

76
00:04:18,691 --> 00:04:22,083
Just check how many villages there are.

77
00:04:22,083 --> 00:04:24,439
Every problem has a way out.

78
00:04:24,439 --> 00:04:26,269
Everyone has a way out, except you and me.

79
00:04:26,269 --> 00:04:28,015
That's right, he's in our way.

80
00:04:28,015 --> 00:04:29,015
Excuse me.

81
00:04:30,528 --> 00:04:31,528
What?

82
00:04:32,442 --> 00:04:34,114
Could you please make way for us?

83
00:04:35,593 --> 00:04:37,942
Well, go ahead.

84
00:04:37,942 --> 00:04:39,852
Why don't you just walk? Why are you asking me?

85
00:04:39,852 --> 00:04:42,843
Well, you've been in our way for half an hour now.

86
00:04:42,843 --> 00:04:47,153
How so? I was dealing with work earlier. I'm a society representative.

87
00:04:47,153 --> 00:04:49,581
People's problems always come first.

88
00:04:49,581 --> 00:04:51,132
You only work on a plane...

89
00:04:51,132 --> 00:04:54,726
how would you know anything about our society's problems?

90
00:04:54,726 --> 00:04:56,798
What's going on now?

91
00:04:56,798 --> 00:04:59,261
Well, our chickens won't lay eggs.

92
00:04:59,261 --> 00:05:01,575
So the villagers played them some songs.

93
00:05:03,082 --> 00:05:05,156
And what happened?

94
00:05:05,156 --> 00:05:10,506
They played heartbreak tracks so the chickens cried.

95
00:05:10,506 --> 00:05:11,659
They were sad.

96
00:05:11,659 --> 00:05:13,485
How did you fix that problem?

97
00:05:13,485 --> 00:05:16,830
I played love songs instead.

98
00:05:16,830 --> 00:05:20,829
Then, the chickens had some sexual urges, making babies and laying eggs all day and night.

99
00:05:21,822 --> 00:05:22,411
That's good.

100
00:05:22,411 --> 00:05:25,273
So this time we switched to playing rock music.

101
00:05:25,273 --> 00:05:27,628
When we played rock music for the chickens,

102
00:05:27,628 --> 00:05:29,017
the chickens all started dancing.

103
00:05:29,017 --> 00:05:31,005
Then, they trampled each other to death.

104
00:05:31,005 --> 00:05:33,119
Some fought and died.

105
00:05:33,119 --> 00:05:34,953
So how did you solve this problem, then?

106
00:05:34,953 --> 00:05:37,548
We bet on tiger, shrimp, and gourd.

107
00:05:37,548 --> 00:05:39,414
Instead of the chicken, that's how.

108
00:05:39,414 --> 00:05:40,480
And what if it lands on gourd?

109
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:43,509
Then you put your money on frog, fish, and shrimp.

110
00:05:43,509 --> 00:05:46,375
And what if it lays triple on tiger or something?

111
00:05:46,375 --> 00:05:47,801
This part is important.

112
00:05:48,393 --> 00:05:49,466
No, that's not it.

113
00:05:49,466 --> 00:05:51,453
I’m the provincial representative, you know.

114
00:05:51,453 --> 00:05:54,648
There's no way I'd ever be involved in gambling, not at all.

115
00:05:54,648 --> 00:05:58,314
Oh, okay.

116
00:05:58,314 --> 00:06:00,260
Then, please.

117
00:06:00,260 --> 00:06:01,935
Please go ahead.

118
00:06:01,935 --> 00:06:02,844
Okay, okay, okay.

119
00:06:02,844 --> 00:06:04,796
Alright, I'll keep going.

120
00:06:04,796 --> 00:06:07,266
No, no, no, tiger! Tiger and frog!

121
00:06:07,266 --> 00:06:09,421
Are we that free? We just listened to chicken farming stories.

122
00:06:09,421 --> 00:06:10,968
Now, I want to eat chicken.

123
00:06:10,968 --> 00:06:13,436
I'll go back and listen to heartbroken chickens first.

124
00:06:13,436 --> 00:06:14,136
I want to eat heartbroken chicken.

125
00:06:20,193 --> 00:06:21,501
This one, huh?

126
00:06:21,501 --> 00:06:23,409
Yeah, I bought it.

127
00:06:23,409 --> 00:06:25,036
They said eight thousand with delivery.

128
00:06:25,036 --> 00:06:26,036
So I told them to park it here.

129
00:06:28,062 --> 00:06:29,062
Even two thousand I’d think twice.

130
00:06:30,934 --> 00:06:31,934
I don’t think we’re gonna make it.

131
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:37,031
Here you are! No parking here, you know.

132
00:06:37,031 --> 00:06:38,739
We’re just leaving now, sir, sorry about that.

133
00:06:38,739 --> 00:06:40,210
We’re in a hurry, officer.

134
00:06:40,210 --> 00:06:41,280
We’re gonna get killed, sir.

135
00:06:41,280 --> 00:06:43,795
Huh? Get killed?

136
00:06:43,795 --> 00:06:44,795
Go, go, go, go!

137
00:06:46,863 --> 00:06:47,456
Go do a urine test.

138
00:06:47,456 --> 00:06:48,244
What?

139
00:06:48,244 --> 00:06:49,239
High on drugs, huh?

140
00:06:49,239 --> 00:06:51,026
Officer, I’m telling the truth.

141
00:06:51,026 --> 00:06:52,299
We’re really gonna get killed.

142
00:06:52,299 --> 00:06:55,806
Yeah, you’ll be killed, for the fine.

143
00:06:55,806 --> 00:06:57,595
Officer, we’re really not on drugs.

144
00:06:57,595 --> 00:06:59,595
Then let me search the car and both of you.

145
00:07:02,183 --> 00:07:05,176
Good thing there’s nothing illegal in the car.

146
00:07:05,176 --> 00:07:06,201
There is, you idiot.

147
00:07:06,201 --> 00:07:06,633
What?

148
00:07:06,633 --> 00:07:08,509
I got Madam Porn’s gun on me.

149
00:07:08,509 --> 00:07:09,509
Shit!

150
00:07:12,582 --> 00:07:16,581
Nothing in the car? Then, let me search you.

151
00:07:17,928 --> 00:07:19,928
Hey, pretty boy, come here, hands up.

152
00:07:26,435 --> 00:07:27,435
Nothing on you.

153
00:07:27,989 --> 00:07:28,989
Move over here.

154
00:07:36,733 --> 00:07:40,637
Urgent! Armed robbery at the gold shop, requesting backup.

155
00:07:40,637 --> 00:07:41,636
Copy.

156
00:07:44,225 --> 00:07:46,225
Here’s your ticket, go pay your fine.

157
00:07:51,257 --> 00:07:53,568
Kreetha, All-New, where are you two headed?

158
00:07:53,568 --> 00:07:55,760
Well, we...

159
00:07:55,760 --> 00:07:58,388
Oh, we got something to do in Bangna.

160
00:07:58,388 --> 00:08:01,218
Perfect! I was just about to go buy chive dumplings there.

161
00:08:01,218 --> 00:08:02,092
Let me ride with you.

162
00:08:02,092 --> 00:08:05,765
But before Bangna, we have to run an errand at Rama 2 first.

163
00:08:05,765 --> 00:08:08,953
Oh Rama 2! I have to go drop off my share payment there too.

164
00:08:08,953 --> 00:08:10,142
Let me ride along, okay?

165
00:08:10,142 --> 00:08:10,896
Is that a good idea?

166
00:08:10,896 --> 00:08:13,689
Of course, I'll go with you.

167
00:08:13,689 --> 00:08:14,689
Sorry, we can’t.

168
00:08:16,679 --> 00:08:20,678
So stingy! Alright, I’ll just hitch a ride with a truck then.

169
00:08:34,346 --> 00:08:37,297
What kind of shitty flight roster is this?

170
00:08:37,297 --> 00:08:39,652
This week off to Europe, next week off to Africa...

171
00:08:39,652 --> 00:08:41,960
And the week after that...to the Middle East. Are you insane?

172
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:45,705
So what?

173
00:08:45,705 --> 00:08:49,053
I've told you already I want short-haul right now.

174
00:08:49,053 --> 00:08:51,769
Like Japan or Korea or something.

175
00:08:51,769 --> 00:08:56,768
I know why you wanna go to Japan. You’re hooking up with Captain Kubo, right?

176
00:08:57,867 --> 00:09:01,094
Who? What?

177
00:09:01,094 --> 00:09:05,093
Yeah, and if I am, so what?

178
00:09:05,528 --> 00:09:06,635
Jealous?

179
00:09:06,635 --> 00:09:08,183
I’m not jealous.

180
00:09:08,183 --> 00:09:10,182
I just can’t stand you, I can’t stand your face.

181
00:09:12,456 --> 00:09:14,727
Get back to work, stop being difficult.

182
00:09:14,727 --> 00:09:16,954
Wow, I'm feeling good today.

183
00:09:16,954 --> 00:09:18,953
I'm gonna get some coffee now.

184
00:09:20,340 --> 00:09:21,340
Tid-Gift!

185
00:09:23,173 --> 00:09:26,399
Uncle, there’s no one by that name here.

186
00:09:26,399 --> 00:09:29,224
There’s no one with the name you’re looking for.

187
00:09:29,224 --> 00:09:31,170
He says he works here, dear.

188
00:09:31,170 --> 00:09:33,005
Nope, there’s no one with that name at all.

189
00:09:33,005 --> 00:09:35,081
Hey, isn’t that…

190
00:09:35,081 --> 00:09:37,425
the uncle we met at the airport.

191
00:09:37,425 --> 00:09:40,890
Yeah, he said he’s looking for his son.

192
00:09:40,890 --> 00:09:41,926
Looking for his son?

193
00:09:41,926 --> 00:09:43,675
Um, what’s your son’s name, uncle?

194
00:09:43,675 --> 00:09:45,302
Nhon.

195
00:09:45,302 --> 00:09:46,847
His name is Nhon. Nhon.

196
00:09:46,847 --> 00:09:47,962
Bak Nhon.

197
00:09:47,962 --> 00:09:48,752
No one named Bak Nhon here.

198
00:09:48,752 --> 00:09:49,865
Uncle, maybe try calling him?

199
00:09:49,865 --> 00:09:51,084
Can’t get through at all, dear.

200
00:09:51,084 --> 00:09:53,118
He changes his number all the time.

201
00:09:53,118 --> 00:09:54,740
What’s all the noise?

202
00:09:54,740 --> 00:09:58,376
This isn’t a marketplace, you know.

203
00:09:58,376 --> 00:09:59,245
Dad.

204
00:09:59,245 --> 00:09:59,949
Nhon!

205
00:09:59,949 --> 00:10:01,422
Dad.

206
00:10:01,422 --> 00:10:02,422
How’d you get here?

207
00:10:08,571 --> 00:10:11,640
Sit down, sit down.

208
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:14,149
Bak Nhon.

209
00:10:14,819 --> 00:10:16,495
This is my Dad.

210
00:10:16,495 --> 00:10:17,442
Your Dad?

211
00:10:17,442 --> 00:10:18,442
Don’t we look alike?

212
00:10:22,156 --> 00:10:23,465
They’re talking.

213
00:10:23,465 --> 00:10:25,771
Using their eyebrows to talk.

214
00:10:31,238 --> 00:10:32,424
Missed you so much!

215
00:10:32,424 --> 00:10:34,380
What kind of communication is that?

216
00:10:34,380 --> 00:10:37,095
It’s been ages since you’ve come home.

217
00:10:37,095 --> 00:10:39,121
I've been really busy, Dad.

218
00:10:39,121 --> 00:10:41,592
Yeah, work is really busy but...

219
00:10:41,592 --> 00:10:43,020
Come home once in a while.

220
00:10:43,020 --> 00:10:44,490
Look, Dad.

221
00:10:44,490 --> 00:10:46,398
There are lots of work to be done.

222
00:10:46,398 --> 00:10:47,871
Yeah…it’s just…

223
00:10:47,871 --> 00:10:48,660
Nhon.

224
00:10:48,660 --> 00:10:49,286
Yes?

225
00:10:49,286 --> 00:10:50,353
Let me ask you.

226
00:10:50,353 --> 00:10:51,986
What are you gonna do about…

227
00:10:51,986 --> 00:10:53,575
what you promised me?

228
00:10:53,575 --> 00:10:55,285
What are you gonna do?

229
00:10:55,285 --> 00:10:56,352
About what?

230
00:10:56,352 --> 00:10:59,143
Your wife, of course. What’s your plan?

231
00:10:59,143 --> 00:11:01,207
Uh, that…that thing…

232
00:11:01,207 --> 00:11:02,959
Spit it out, don’t mumble.

233
00:11:02,959 --> 00:11:04,269
Because I need to start getting people ready...

234
00:11:04,269 --> 00:11:07,498
Slaughter some pigs and cows and feed the guests.

235
00:11:10,715 --> 00:11:11,905
There, there.

236
00:11:11,905 --> 00:11:13,574
These two right here.

237
00:11:13,574 --> 00:11:14,805
I think they’re pretty good.

238
00:11:15,245 --> 00:11:18,113
Which type do you like, Dad?

239
00:11:18,113 --> 00:11:20,264
That one!

240
00:11:22,010 --> 00:11:23,559
That's my type.

241
00:11:23,559 --> 00:11:25,586
Me?

242
00:11:25,586 --> 00:11:26,694
If you get that girl,

243
00:11:26,694 --> 00:11:28,086
easy births...

244
00:11:28,086 --> 00:11:31,557
about once a year.

245
00:11:31,557 --> 00:11:32,224
Are you serious, Dad?

246
00:11:32,917 --> 00:11:34,350
I like this type.

247
00:11:34,350 --> 00:11:36,418
Your Mom keeps pestering me.

248
00:11:36,418 --> 00:11:37,117
We want to hold a grandchild already.

249
00:11:41,329 --> 00:11:42,840
Where the hell should we go?

250
00:11:42,840 --> 00:11:45,840
Anywhere, or we’re gonna get silenced for sure.

251
00:11:46,950 --> 00:11:47,949
Let’s go to Bangna.

252
00:11:48,020 --> 00:11:49,020
Shit.

253
00:11:49,727 --> 00:11:51,476
How did you get here?

254
00:11:51,476 --> 00:11:53,864
I snuck in just now.

255
00:11:53,864 --> 00:11:57,863
So who’s killing who again?

256
00:11:58,483 --> 00:12:01,674
Oh, we’re talking about a game.

257
00:12:01,674 --> 00:12:03,620
I haven’t had many flights lately.

258
00:12:03,620 --> 00:12:05,488
I've been bored in my room.

259
00:12:05,488 --> 00:12:06,488
Let me tag along, okay?

260
00:12:09,874 --> 00:12:12,306
You think we’ll survive?

261
00:12:12,306 --> 00:12:14,305
A pro hitman can easily tail us.

262
00:12:15,780 --> 00:12:17,250
So what do we do?

263
00:12:17,250 --> 00:12:20,038
As far as I know, they like to disguise themselves to get close to the target.

264
00:12:20,038 --> 00:12:21,038
Disguise?

265
00:12:22,095 --> 00:12:27,094
Yeah, so we can’t talk to strangers at all to keep ourselves safe.

266
00:12:34,085 --> 00:12:35,393
Chicken skewers, ten baht!

267
00:12:35,393 --> 00:12:36,621
This could be one of them...

268
00:12:36,621 --> 00:12:38,527
Killers in disguise.

269
00:12:38,527 --> 00:12:39,717
Do you have chicken butts?

270
00:12:39,717 --> 00:12:41,067
No butts, sorry.

271
00:12:41,067 --> 00:12:44,856
Then one gizzard and ten bags of sticky rice.

272
00:12:44,856 --> 00:12:46,806
Sky, why are you having chicken now?

273
00:12:46,806 --> 00:12:48,805
I’m hungry. Haven’t had breakfast yet.

274
00:12:50,512 --> 00:12:53,456
Basically, right now, you and I can’t trust anyone.

275
00:12:53,456 --> 00:12:55,455
Don’t let anyone get near us, seriously.

276
00:12:57,366 --> 00:12:58,366
What the hell is this?

277
00:13:00,032 --> 00:13:00,899
It’s for cutting the sauce packet.

278
00:13:00,899 --> 00:13:01,899
It’s fine, I’ll just bite it open.

279
00:13:02,567 --> 00:13:03,567
Thank you.

280
00:13:03,922 --> 00:13:04,552
Sure.

281
00:13:04,552 --> 00:13:05,552
You guys get scared so easily.

282
00:13:06,341 --> 00:13:08,341
Light’s green, can we go yet?

283
00:13:13,157 --> 00:13:15,951
Shit, these hitmen are cold-blooded.

284
00:13:15,951 --> 00:13:17,951
They could poison the food.

285
00:13:20,660 --> 00:13:21,660
Hey!

286
00:13:21,815 --> 00:13:23,815
Shit! Look, Sky’s hit. Poisoned already!

287
00:13:24,966 --> 00:13:26,233
I need some water.

288
00:13:26,233 --> 00:13:28,061
Water, water, water!

289
00:13:28,061 --> 00:13:29,061
Chicken gizzard’s stuck in my throat.

290
00:13:35,688 --> 00:13:36,442
Shit!

291
00:13:36,442 --> 00:13:38,469
Who’s lighting firecrackers?

292
00:13:38,469 --> 00:13:40,342
Firecrackers my ass, we’re getting shot at!

293
00:13:40,342 --> 00:13:41,342
Huh?

294
00:13:42,214 --> 00:13:43,214
Who?

295
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:47,349
Who’s chasing and shooting at you guys anyway?

296
00:13:47,349 --> 00:13:49,349
Did you honk at someone or something?

297
00:14:03,998 --> 00:14:04,904
Nhon.

298
00:14:04,904 --> 00:14:05,451
Yes?

299
00:14:05,451 --> 00:14:08,480
When are you gonna give me grandkids to hold?

300
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:10,996
Calm down, Dad. Work’s been crazy.

301
00:14:10,996 --> 00:14:13,942
I’m old now, got all these illnesses.

302
00:14:13,942 --> 00:14:15,853
Don’t know when I’ll die.

303
00:14:15,853 --> 00:14:18,244
Dad, you’re still healthy.

304
00:14:18,244 --> 00:14:20,660
I only have one child.

305
00:14:20,660 --> 00:14:22,659
At least, give me a grandkid to hold.

306
00:14:28,007 --> 00:14:29,515
Hey, Tid-Gift.

307
00:14:29,515 --> 00:14:32,261
Were you eavesdropping on them?

308
00:14:32,261 --> 00:14:34,933
So rude. No manners.

309
00:14:34,933 --> 00:14:36,756
His Dad wanting grandkids...

310
00:14:36,756 --> 00:14:38,829
that’s their family business.

311
00:14:38,829 --> 00:14:39,903
Why do you have to meddle?

312
00:14:39,903 --> 00:14:43,057
Wow, look at you with all the manners.

313
00:14:43,057 --> 00:14:44,886
You remember every detail.

314
00:14:44,886 --> 00:14:47,272
Well, his Dad is sick, near death, with all kinds of diseases.

315
00:14:47,272 --> 00:14:50,017
He could die today or tomorrow. Don’t you feel sorry for him?

316
00:14:50,017 --> 00:14:51,250
Wow, know-it-all much.

317
00:14:51,250 --> 00:14:54,642
I just really care about people, okay? I’m not…

318
00:14:54,642 --> 00:14:55,313
Nosey!

319
00:14:55,313 --> 00:14:55,823
I’m not!

320
00:14:55,823 --> 00:14:56,822
No, no, no!

321
00:14:59,973 --> 00:15:00,973
I know what I’m gonna do next.

322
00:15:06,097 --> 00:15:07,096
Hello, Dad.

323
00:15:07,686 --> 00:15:08,686
Hello there.

324
00:15:09,116 --> 00:15:12,872
My name’s Tid-Gift. I’m Chai's co-worker.

325
00:15:12,872 --> 00:15:14,941
Oh, really?

326
00:15:14,941 --> 00:15:17,940
And I also used to be his bed buddy.

327
00:15:21,376 --> 00:15:22,922
What the hell, Tid-Gift?

328
00:15:22,922 --> 00:15:26,922
I know he wanted to keep this a secret.

329
00:15:27,432 --> 00:15:28,381
It’s okay, dear. If there’s anything…

330
00:15:28,381 --> 00:15:29,731
But I have to tell you.

331
00:15:29,731 --> 00:15:32,201
You can tell me anything.

332
00:15:32,201 --> 00:15:38,199
We liked each other and then accidentally…

333
00:15:39,589 --> 00:15:42,420
Accidentally slept together, Dad.

334
00:15:42,420 --> 00:15:43,490
She’s lying, Dad.

335
00:15:43,490 --> 00:15:44,402
Stop talking!

336
00:15:44,402 --> 00:15:47,356
You slept with her, now take responsibility.

337
00:15:47,356 --> 00:15:51,221
She’s a young woman with feelings, with parents.

338
00:15:51,221 --> 00:15:53,220
Goddamn it.

339
00:15:57,877 --> 00:16:00,790
So, how many positions did he do with you?

340
00:16:00,790 --> 00:16:01,860
Countless, Dad.

341
00:16:01,860 --> 00:16:02,571
This is not funny.

342
00:16:02,571 --> 00:16:04,570
I'm not being funny, Chai.

343
00:16:07,162 --> 00:16:09,161
He screwed me and dumped me, Dad...

344
00:16:10,909 --> 00:16:12,409
It’s not true, Dad.

345
00:16:12,816 --> 00:16:13,815
It’s not true!

346
00:16:17,863 --> 00:16:18,815
Help!

347
00:16:19,207 --> 00:16:21,523
Shit, I shouldn't have gotten in this car.

348
00:16:21,523 --> 00:16:23,474
So what should we do? Ditch the car and run?

349
00:16:23,474 --> 00:16:26,181
If we do that, we won't make it.

350
00:16:26,181 --> 00:16:28,210
Should we go to Bangna first and take Sky there?

351
00:16:28,210 --> 00:16:30,209
Let's go. We should get out of this direction. Hurry up!

352
00:16:31,718 --> 00:16:34,950
We only got one way that will make us live.

353
00:16:34,950 --> 00:16:36,142
We gotta fight her!

354
00:16:36,142 --> 00:16:37,737
You guys got a gun?

355
00:16:37,737 --> 00:16:39,736
Well, it came with the car.

356
00:16:40,808 --> 00:16:42,476
I don't know how to use it.

357
00:16:42,476 --> 00:16:43,267
Sky!

358
00:16:43,267 --> 00:16:45,266
Don't point the gun at me. I don't know how to shoot, no.

359
00:16:46,739 --> 00:16:48,739
If you don't shoot, we won't make it.

360
00:16:48,806 --> 00:16:49,805
So what do I do?

361
00:16:50,002 --> 00:16:51,002
Cock it first.

362
00:16:51,717 --> 00:16:52,717
Then what?

363
00:16:53,268 --> 00:16:55,615
Done and then what?

364
00:16:55,615 --> 00:16:57,954
Cock the gun, not Ram Wong (Thai dancing)

365
00:16:57,954 --> 00:16:59,953
You do it. I can't. I'm scared.

366
00:17:04,062 --> 00:17:04,809
How was it?

367
00:17:04,809 --> 00:17:06,557
I don't know. I shot with my eyes closed.

368
00:17:06,557 --> 00:17:10,556
What? How are you gonna hit anything with your eyes closed? Just shoot!

369
00:17:12,228 --> 00:17:12,774
That...fell.

370
00:17:12,774 --> 00:17:13,774
Yay!

371
00:17:14,571 --> 00:17:15,570
The gun fell.

372
00:17:16,242 --> 00:17:17,720
Oh my god, you idiot.

373
00:17:17,720 --> 00:17:19,553
How the hell did the gun just fall like that?

374
00:17:19,553 --> 00:17:20,939
All-New was driving too fast.

375
00:17:20,939 --> 00:17:22,939
Next time, I'll make you carry a slingshot, you asshole.

376
00:17:25,685 --> 00:17:26,685
What now?

377
00:17:28,719 --> 00:17:29,719
Found it.

378
00:17:30,271 --> 00:17:31,271
Hey!

379
00:17:31,623 --> 00:17:33,443
The Luang Pho Mun phallic amulet...

380
00:17:33,443 --> 00:17:35,111
Famous temple in Bang Bua Thong...

381
00:17:35,111 --> 00:17:36,378
Its blessing protects you.

382
00:17:36,814 --> 00:17:38,046
It keeps you safe from harm.

383
00:17:38,476 --> 00:17:39,476
I'll handle this myself.

384
00:17:49,066 --> 00:17:50,066
She lost control.

385
00:17:51,175 --> 00:17:52,175
So we're safe now, right?

386
00:17:52,369 --> 00:17:53,369
That was awesome, Sky.

387
00:17:54,163 --> 00:17:55,163
I did well, right?

388
00:17:59,829 --> 00:18:00,828
Wait, why is the car slowing down?

389
00:18:02,770 --> 00:18:03,770
Seems like we're running out of gas.

390
00:18:03,885 --> 00:18:04,560
Huh?

391
00:18:04,560 --> 00:18:06,059
Why the hell are we running out now?

392
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:10,247
What do we do? There's no gas station here.

393
00:18:10,247 --> 00:18:12,246
Wherever you're going, hurry up.

394
00:18:12,354 --> 00:18:13,354
She's gonna catch up. Hurry!

395
00:18:13,583 --> 00:18:15,583
I think we should loop back and regroup.

396
00:18:18,933 --> 00:18:20,933
Why run out now?

397
00:18:23,269 --> 00:18:25,735
I messed up myself, Dad.

398
00:18:25,735 --> 00:18:27,734
I was the one who let Chai bang me.

399
00:18:30,204 --> 00:18:33,278
Stop acting. My Dad won’t believe you.

400
00:18:33,278 --> 00:18:34,278
I believe that.

401
00:18:35,745 --> 00:18:37,744
Dad, seriously?

402
00:18:38,975 --> 00:18:40,975
How could I not believe such a pretty girl?

403
00:18:42,561 --> 00:18:44,628
But if Chai won’t admit it…

404
00:18:44,628 --> 00:18:46,628
I'm fine with that.

405
00:18:47,902 --> 00:18:49,489
It’s not true, Dad!

406
00:18:49,489 --> 00:18:52,636
Dad, ask your type of girl then.

407
00:18:52,636 --> 00:18:56,636
Chaba, tell my dad that Gift and I fight all the time. Quick.

408
00:18:58,419 --> 00:19:00,174
Help me right now.

409
00:19:00,723 --> 00:19:02,469
What do I get in exchange?

410
00:19:02,469 --> 00:19:05,259
I’ll treat you with one shabu meal.

411
00:19:05,259 --> 00:19:09,258
Just shabu? That’s too cheap.

412
00:19:09,403 --> 00:19:11,352
Then what do you want to eat?

413
00:19:11,352 --> 00:19:15,107
Omakase. That new place behind the office...

414
00:19:15,107 --> 00:19:16,107
Fine.

415
00:19:17,376 --> 00:19:18,375
Deal.

416
00:19:19,210 --> 00:19:21,199
No, Chai!

417
00:19:22,224 --> 00:19:23,613
I’ll tell the truth myself.

418
00:19:23,613 --> 00:19:26,044
Chai, you slept with Tid-Gift. Just admit it.

419
00:19:26,044 --> 00:19:27,594
What the hell, Chaba?

420
00:19:27,594 --> 00:19:30,941
Seriously, that day when you dragged Tid-Gift into the copy room...

421
00:19:30,941 --> 00:19:32,609
to bang...

422
00:19:32,609 --> 00:19:34,678
I saw you two going at it in there, Dad.

423
00:19:34,678 --> 00:19:36,865
Whoa, they did it in the room?

424
00:19:36,865 --> 00:19:39,533
I didn’t think anyone would see.

425
00:19:39,533 --> 00:19:42,208
Shut up, Tid-Gift.

426
00:19:42,208 --> 00:19:45,043
It’s true. Honestly, I almost got banged too.

427
00:19:45,043 --> 00:19:47,233
But I stopped myself in time.

428
00:19:47,233 --> 00:19:48,703
Because this is the company we love.

429
00:19:48,703 --> 00:19:52,703
But I feel sorry for Tid-Gift.

430
00:19:52,971 --> 00:19:54,765
Where the hell did you come from, you starving Nhon?

431
00:19:54,765 --> 00:19:56,441
It's not like that!

432
00:19:57,428 --> 00:19:59,544
What’s wrong with you?

433
00:19:59,544 --> 00:20:00,691
Stop it, Nhon.

434
00:20:00,691 --> 00:20:03,925
As an elder of this household…

435
00:20:03,925 --> 00:20:07,925
I’ll take responsibility for Nhon’s actions, dear.

436
00:20:08,635 --> 00:20:09,224
Thank you, Dad.

437
00:20:09,224 --> 00:20:11,292
Calm down, calm down.

438
00:20:11,292 --> 00:20:12,292
Listen to your Dad, Nhon.

439
00:20:25,140 --> 00:20:26,140
Okay.

440
00:20:27,730 --> 00:20:28,730
Come on, let’s hurry and run.

441
00:20:29,961 --> 00:20:30,961
Wait.

442
00:20:32,227 --> 00:20:33,227
Let me catch my breath first.

443
00:20:34,094 --> 00:20:36,093
We pushed this far, I think we lost her.

444
00:20:39,327 --> 00:20:40,326
But I don’t think so.

445
00:20:44,032 --> 00:20:46,031
Calm down, please don’t shoot.

446
00:20:50,507 --> 00:20:51,507
Hey, Peck.

447
00:20:57,136 --> 00:20:58,136
Hey, Peck.

448
00:20:59,043 --> 00:21:00,042
Peck.

449
00:21:00,120 --> 00:21:01,120
I was wondering who it was.

450
00:21:01,554 --> 00:21:03,554
Where’s the fancy party you’re headed to?

451
00:21:04,903 --> 00:21:05,902
It's none of your business.

452
00:21:06,093 --> 00:21:07,093
Shit.

453
00:21:12,799 --> 00:21:13,985
Didn’t you want to see me?

454
00:21:13,985 --> 00:21:15,252
I didn’t want to see you.

455
00:21:15,252 --> 00:21:17,080
You did. Didn’t you want to see her?

456
00:21:17,080 --> 00:21:19,152
I don’t want to see you. You talk to her first.

457
00:21:19,152 --> 00:21:21,343
Stop arguing. You’re all gonna die here.

458
00:21:21,343 --> 00:21:23,772
All of us? Uh…

459
00:21:23,772 --> 00:21:25,967
Aren’t you having issues? Talk it out slowly.

460
00:21:25,967 --> 00:21:27,113
I don’t want to talk. You talk to her first.

461
00:21:27,113 --> 00:21:28,586
Like I want to, huh? You…

462
00:21:28,586 --> 00:21:30,586
Or should I kill a chicken to scare the monkeys?

463
00:21:32,820 --> 00:21:33,820
Wanna try killing the monkey first?

464
00:21:42,671 --> 00:21:43,671
Hey!

465
00:21:58,010 --> 00:21:59,010
You’ll pay for this, Pong.

466
00:22:01,486 --> 00:22:02,800
Thank you so much for helping us.

467
00:22:02,800 --> 00:22:05,227
By the way, what’s your name?

468
00:22:05,227 --> 00:22:06,255
My name’s Pong.

469
00:22:06,255 --> 00:22:07,810
I’m All-New.

470
00:22:07,810 --> 00:22:09,638
This is Kreetha.

471
00:22:09,638 --> 00:22:11,638
The one passed out down there is Sky.

472
00:22:12,867 --> 00:22:15,220
And how did you know to come help us?

473
00:22:15,220 --> 00:22:17,220
Oh, I’m a cop.

474
00:22:18,410 --> 00:22:19,410
A cop?

475
00:22:20,243 --> 00:22:22,144
And how did you know we were about to be killed?

476
00:22:22,144 --> 00:22:25,019
I’ve been investigating her. Who are you guys?

477
00:22:25,019 --> 00:22:27,177
We’re flight attendants.

478
00:22:27,177 --> 00:22:30,612
Just flight attendants? Why is Peck trying to kill you?

479
00:22:30,612 --> 00:22:33,561
Did you find out some secrets?

480
00:22:33,561 --> 00:22:35,512
Wait, you know Peck?

481
00:22:35,512 --> 00:22:38,864
Of course. Peck is my sister.

482
00:22:38,864 --> 00:22:40,864
Huh? Sister?

483
00:22:49,144 --> 00:22:53,145
You know, this omakase place is pretty good. The fish is so fresh.

484
00:22:54,172 --> 00:22:58,089
Fresh fish, but my wallet’s dry now.

485
00:22:58,089 --> 00:22:59,002
It’s not that dry.

486
00:22:59,002 --> 00:23:02,835
Damn you, never thought in my life I’d eat a ten-thousand-baht meal.

487
00:23:02,835 --> 00:23:06,749
Come on, it’s worth the investment. We got to prank Chai, didn’t we?

488
00:23:06,749 --> 00:23:07,904
Wanna do it again? It was fun.

489
00:23:07,904 --> 00:23:09,739
No way. That’s enough.

490
00:23:09,739 --> 00:23:11,406
It was fun though.

491
00:23:11,406 --> 00:23:12,716
Did you see Chai’s face?

492
00:23:12,716 --> 00:23:13,312
I did.

493
00:23:13,312 --> 00:23:14,220
He was so stunned. So stunned.

494
00:23:14,220 --> 00:23:16,220
Super expensive though. Seriously an expensive lesson.

495
00:23:18,250 --> 00:23:20,250
Come here. Don’t say anything.

496
00:23:23,925 --> 00:23:24,635
Open the bag.

497
00:23:24,635 --> 00:23:26,151
Okay, okay.

498
00:23:26,151 --> 00:23:27,151
Look at this.

499
00:23:38,697 --> 00:23:42,088
My dear, all this gold and five million baht cash.

500
00:23:42,088 --> 00:23:43,161
This is the dowry.

501
00:23:43,161 --> 00:23:44,911
I’m here to ask for your hand...

502
00:23:44,911 --> 00:23:45,911
for Nhon.

503
00:23:47,227 --> 00:23:48,935
Dad, isn’t that too much?

504
00:23:48,935 --> 00:23:51,082
Hey, how can it be too much?

505
00:23:51,082 --> 00:23:54,710
A pretty cow costs money, you know.

506
00:23:54,710 --> 00:23:56,618
Tid-Gift, this is getting out of hand.

507
00:23:56,618 --> 00:23:58,165
This is basically an engagement now.

508
00:23:58,165 --> 00:23:59,560
Maybe you should stop.

509
00:23:59,560 --> 00:24:00,870
We’ve come this far.

510
00:24:00,870 --> 00:24:01,870
Might as well go all the way.

511
00:24:02,903 --> 00:24:06,903
Whoa, Dad. Am I dreaming?

512
00:24:06,980 --> 00:24:08,170
It’s not a dream.

513
00:24:08,170 --> 00:24:10,087
Because I also have to take responsibility.

514
00:24:10,087 --> 00:24:12,000
On behalf of Nhon here.

515
00:24:12,666 --> 00:24:14,666
This has just become an engagement now.

516
00:24:16,100 --> 00:24:17,527
Nhon.

517
00:24:17,527 --> 00:24:19,028
Go put the ring on her.

518
00:24:19,028 --> 00:24:23,028
If it’s an engagement, you have to kneel.

519
00:24:23,141 --> 00:24:24,141
Come on.

520
00:24:24,574 --> 00:24:25,574
Damn you!

521
00:24:25,966 --> 00:24:26,966
Right here, right here.

522
00:24:35,636 --> 00:24:37,505
You’re having fun, huh?

523
00:24:37,505 --> 00:24:39,505
It’s entertaining, honestly.

524
00:24:48,257 --> 00:24:50,257
Oh my god.

525
00:24:51,520 --> 00:24:53,907
My dear, I will tie your wrist now.

526
00:24:53,907 --> 00:24:56,544
May your life be firm, lasting and secure.

527
00:24:56,936 --> 00:24:59,732
Since you’re under the same roof now, come on.

528
00:24:59,732 --> 00:25:00,924
Hold out your hand, dear.

529
00:25:00,924 --> 00:25:01,924
Like this, yeah.

530
00:25:05,299 --> 00:25:08,299
(Thai blessings)

531
00:25:08,847 --> 00:25:10,847
(Thai blessings)

532
00:25:39,891 --> 00:25:43,526
This doesn’t seem like a wedding. It's more like a concert.

533
00:25:43,526 --> 00:25:46,471
Now, you’re officially engaged.

534
00:25:46,471 --> 00:25:49,788
Nhon can start breaking down the Great Wall of China now.

535
00:25:49,788 --> 00:25:51,334
It's legal so it's all good.

536
00:25:51,334 --> 00:25:53,126
Such a pretty daughter-in-law.

537
00:25:53,126 --> 00:25:57,074
The kids will be so cute, right, Nhon?

538
00:25:57,580 --> 00:25:58,580
Yes, yes.

539
00:26:04,811 --> 00:26:07,997
I finished combat training with my sister.

540
00:26:07,997 --> 00:26:09,987
